cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.MA 

The paper proposes two online portfolio selection methods based on contextual bandit algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making problems, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper deals with financial engineering and market datasets, which are relevant to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
